Date: Fri, 15 Jun 2018 20:07:34 +0300
Subject: drm/atomic-helper: Use bitwise or for filling a bitmask
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit
Git-commit: ca52bea9fa8007f837ab4685b98979bbffc33416
Patch-mainline: v4.19-rc1
References: FATE#326289 FATE#326079 FATE#326049 FATE#322398 FATE#326166

Using += to set the bits in a mask looks funny. It works in this case
because we never set the same bit twice. But let's switch to |= to
make this look more regular.

Cc: Maarten Lankhorst <maarten.lankhorst@linux.intel.com>
